<span id="freeTextContainer143949761358338529"><br/><b>It isn&apos;t about being or not being dead, it&apos;s about what you leave behind...</b><br/><br/>To me Katurian&apos;s effort to save his stories and his confidence in his stories was adorable. I always wonder what trace am I capable of leaving behind?<br/>Katurian somehow reminds me of Hans Christian Andersen and his stories like the little match girl, which is a total catastrophe. As it is stated through the story, the storyteller just tells a story and is not responsible for any implication made by his/her readers, yet I th</span>
  <span id="freeText143949761358338529" style="display:none"><br /><b>It isn't about being or not being dead, it's about what you leave behind...</b><br /><br />To me Katurian's effort to save his stories and his confidence in his stories was adorable. I always wonder what trace am I capable of leaving behind?<br />Katurian somehow reminds me of Hans Christian Andersen and his stories like the little match girl, which is a total catastrophe. As it is stated through the story, the storyteller just tells a story and is not responsible for any implication made by his/her readers, yet I think when the story is gonna deal with kids you gotta be more cautious. </span>
