  <span id="freeText10345242965302133269" style="display:none">I was going to give this three out of five, since almost all of the events in the first two acts were disappointingly predictable; but the ending was brilliant, a great "twist", as Katurian would probably call it. Not only a twist in plot, but a twist in theme , in characterization, in the whole worldview of the story. <br />PS. Oh,and I forgot to add: IT WAS THE SICKEST AND SIMULTANEOUSLY GENTLEST STORY I HAVE EVER READ. Is that even possible? Apparently, it is. </span>
