<span id="freeTextContainer886850060182835029">3.5/5 Stars<br/><br/>I had to read this play for class and I must say I was pleasantly surprised. I liked how the author included so many stories into the main narrative, my favourite was probably the Pillowman one, but every single one of them had its own importance in the main storyline. Just to be clear, the stories aren&apos;t nice in any way, they are about murdered children, so it&apos;s a lot to read. <br/>I wish this play could have had a different ending, but in a way I get it.<br/>I will try and see if I can find a</span>
  <span id="freeText886850060182835029" style="display:none">3.5/5 Stars<br /><br />I had to read this play for class and I must say I was pleasantly surprised. I liked how the author included so many stories into the main narrative, my favourite was probably the Pillowman one, but every single one of them had its own importance in the main storyline. Just to be clear, the stories aren't nice in any way, they are about murdered children, so it's a lot to read. <br />I wish this play could have had a different ending, but in a way I get it.<br />I will try and see if I can find an actual recording of this play because I would love to see it acted on stage.<br /></span>
