  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1501353364" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1501353364" />
    <a title="Gull" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43757020-gull"><img alt="Gull" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1485199675p2/43757020.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1501353364?book_show_action=true">Jan 08, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gull" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gull" href="/user/show/43757020-gull">Gull</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/43757020-gull?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/43757020-gull?shelf=6-stars">6-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/43757020-gull?shelf=horror">horror</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/43757020-gull?shelf=drama">drama</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/43757020-gull?shelf=plays">plays</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1501353364" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2582874245989845787">I absolutely <b>LOVE</b> this play! It is ridiculously amazing, and has earned its place up there amongst my all time favourites!<br/><br/><i>The Pillowman</i> is mind-blowingly dark, disturbing, and refreshingly original. It is both humorous and tragic. I think the humour comes from the condescension and irony, while it is tragic due to the central subject matter. The ending is shocking, in a strangely positive yet disturbing way. I had goose pimples throughout!<br/><br/>Katurian’s stories, largely involving the torture of chil</span>
  <span id="freeText2582874245989845787" style="display:none">I absolutely <b>LOVE</b> this play! It is ridiculously amazing, and has earned its place up there amongst my all time favourites!<br /><br /><i>The Pillowman</i> is mind-blowingly dark, disturbing, and refreshingly original. It is both humorous and tragic. I think the humour comes from the condescension and irony, while it is tragic due to the central subject matter. The ending is shocking, in a strangely positive yet disturbing way. I had goose pimples throughout!<br /><br />Katurian’s stories, largely involving the torture of children, inspire his brother to reproduce the horrors. Yet, as messed up as Katurian’s brother is, the final act of treating a mute girl pleasantly in accordance with one of Katurian’s stories, ‘The Little Green Pig’, illustrates that, perhaps, he was just <i>misguidedly</i> acting out the stories he read; this ultimately shows that literature—and by extension art—can stimulate people in both a positive way and a negative way.<br /><br /><i>The Pillowman</i> functions as a play dealing with totalitarianism, and <b>literary censure</b>, and so it is reminiscent of books like Bradbury’s <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4381.Fahrenheit_451" title="Fahrenheit 451 by Ray Bradbury" rel="nofollow noopener">Fahrenheit 451</a>.<br /><br />It is a definite must-read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="2582874245989845787" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1501353364">
