<div id="review_64197228" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/64197228" />
    <a title="Iris" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1440073-iris"><img alt="Iris" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1604630344p2/1440073.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/64197228?book_show_action=true">Jul 20, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Iris" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Iris" href="/user/show/1440073-iris">Iris</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780822221005" href="/book/show/336283.The_Pillowman">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Iris by: </span>
      my neighbor (who is perplexed by her fixation on this play)
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer64197228" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10811200792872202014">This play - first performed in London in 2003 - is a devastating experiment. I would especially recommend it to reluctant readers. Though a veteran reader will pore over it in two or three sittings, the themes of the play sink in slowly and subtly. It encourages a reader to imagine alternate explanations for horrific events, and seek ways out of irrevocable situations. <br/><br/>To write more about &quot;The Pillowman&quot; is to give away surprises and twists in in the plot and the storytelling. Better to see for </span>
  <span id="freeText10811200792872202014" style="display:none">This play - first performed in London in 2003 - is a devastating experiment. I would especially recommend it to reluctant readers. Though a veteran reader will pore over it in two or three sittings, the themes of the play sink in slowly and subtly. It encourages a reader to imagine alternate explanations for horrific events, and seek ways out of irrevocable situations. <br /><br />To write more about "The Pillowman" is to give away surprises and twists in in the plot and the storytelling. Better to see for yourself the shifts in your understanding of the pillowman, the writer, his brother and interrogators.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10811200792872202014" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


