    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_131715354" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/131715354" />
    <a title="Rick" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/764994-rick"><img alt="Rick" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1289746453p2/764994.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/131715354?book_show_action=true">Nov 20, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rick" href="/user/show/764994-rick">Rick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/764994-rick?shelf=drama">drama</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer131715354" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9411073117029761005">Two police detectives in a totalitarian state question two brothers, one a writer and one who is, as they say, “backward.” “A little slow,” counters his protective brother. The writer, perhaps in homage to Joseph Heller and his character Major Major Major, who when drafted in the air force is promoted to Major to avoid him being Airman Major Major or Lt. Major Major, has the same three names, Katurian Katurian Katurian. Katurian has no idea why he’s been arrested and is distressed when he discov</span>
  <span id="freeText9411073117029761005" style="display:none">Two police detectives in a totalitarian state question two brothers, one a writer and one who is, as they say, “backward.” “A little slow,” counters his protective brother. The writer, perhaps in homage to Joseph Heller and his character Major Major Major, who when drafted in the air force is promoted to Major to avoid him being Airman Major Major or Lt. Major Major, has the same three names, Katurian Katurian Katurian. Katurian has no idea why he’s been arrested and is distressed when he discovers his brother was also arrested. Based on the aggressive, at time violent questioning it seems to have something to do with the short stories Katurian writes, many of which feature children as murder victims. The play unfolds with layers of surprises and shifting understandings. Some of the surprises are anticipated but it doesn’t matter because surprise wasn’t the point. Despite thrilling moments, this is not a thriller or a comedy, despite some laugh out loud moments. It’s a complex drama of individuals, responsibility, and the tangled affects of circumstance. And it is also very much about storytelling, its importance, and, oddly, its risks. McDonagh has such a gift for plotting, character, dialogue that he amazes with how deftly he pulls off the absurd, the macabre, the compassionate. He is a literary magician and this is a stunning, darkly imaginative and profound drama.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9411073117029761005" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

